1 committee, pursuant to section 5-5-217, MCA, to examine how the Department of Public Health and Human
2 Services and the Office of Public Instruction can best coordinate their efforts to address the health and learning
3 needs of children who had prenatal exposure to methamphetamine and fentanyl.
4 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that the committee:
5 (1) collaborate in this study with:
6 (a) the Department of Public Health and Human Services;
7 (b) the Office of Public Instruction;
8 (c) tribal governments;
9 (d) county and tribal health departments; and
10 (e) early childhood care providers and education providers.
11 (2) gather, compile, and review statistics on the number of children who had prenatal exposure to
12 methamphetamine and fentanyl;
13 (3) investigate ways other states have addressed the health and learning needs of children who
14 had prenatal exposure to methamphetamine and fentanyl; and
15 (4) develop proposals in collaboration with the Department of Public Health and Human Services
16 and the Office of Public Instruction for a coordinated response to effectively address the health and learning
17 needs of children who had prenatal exposure to methamphetamine and fentanyl.
18 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that all aspects of the study, including presentation and review
19 requirements, be concluded prior to September 15, 2026.
20 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that the final results of the study, including any findings, conclusions,
21 comments, or recommendations of the appropriate committee, be reported to the 70th Legislature.
